## Installation

### Step 1 — Build the JS assets

```bash
cd wp-agent-ai
npm install
npm run build
```

The `build/` directory will be created with compiled JS and CSS.

### Step 2 — Upload to WordPress

**Option A — File upload:**
Copy the entire `/wp-agent-ai` folder (including `/build`) to:
```
/wp-content/plugins/wp-agent-ai/
```

**Option B — Zip upload:**
Zip the folder, then go to **WordPress Admin → Plugins → Add New → Upload Plugin**.

### Step 3 — Activate

Go to **WordPress Admin → Plugins** and activate **WP Agent AI – Landing Page Writer**.

### Step 4 — Configure

1. Navigate to **WP Agent AI → Settings**
2. Enter your **OpenRouter API key** (get one free at [openrouter.ai/keys](https://openrouter.ai/keys))
3. Select your preferred **AI model**
4. Click **Test Connection** to verify everything works
5. Set default tone and length (optional)
6. Click **Save Settings**

---

## Using the Block

1. Open any **Post or Page** in the Gutenberg editor
2. Click **+** to add a block → search for **"AI Landing Page Writer"** (under the *WP Agent AI* category)
3. Fill in your **Business Description**
4. Choose **Section Type**, **Tone**, and **Length**
5. Click **✦ Generate Content**
6. Blocks are inserted directly below — edit, style, and rearrange them like any Gutenberg block

### Regenerating

After the first generation, a **Refinement Instructions** panel appears. Describe what to change (e.g. "make the headline shorter, focus on enterprise") then click **↺ Regenerate**.

