## Security

- All REST requests require the `edit_posts` capability + valid WP REST nonce
- Admin AJAX requires `manage_options` + nonce check via `check_ajax_referer()`
- API key stored in WordPress options table — never exposed to the browser
- All inputs sanitized with `sanitize_textarea_field()` / `sanitize_text_field()`
- All outputs escaped with `esc_html()`, `esc_attr()`, `esc_url()`
- No secrets hardcoded anywhere in the codebase

